🔐 1. Staff
POST → /api/staff/register

Registers a new staff account.

{
  "fullName": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "phone": "09123456789",
  "role": "admin",
  "password": "123456"
}

POST → /api/staff/login

Logs in a staff member and returns a JWT token.

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "123456"
}


✅ Save the returned token in your Postman “Environment Variables” as {{token}}.

🏛 2. Chapel
GET → /api/chapel/

Gets all chapels.
Headers:

Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

GET → /api/chapel/available

Gets all chapels where status = 'Available'.
(No token required)

POST → /api/chapel/

Creates a new chapel.
Headers:

Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


Body:

{
  "chapelName": "Saint Mary Chapel",
  "description": "Main chapel for ceremonies"
}

PUT → /api/chapel/status

Updates the chapel’s status.
Headers:

Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


Body:

{
  "chapelID": 1,
  "status": "Unavailable"
}

🌐 Base URL
http://localhost:5000